# Euclid Example: Calculus

## Trigonometry

- Identity: `$sin(THETA)^2 + cos(THETA)^2 = 1$`
- Inverse trig: `$arcsin(x) + arccos(x) = PI \\ 2$`

## Differential and Integral Forms

- Derivative: `$diff(f(x), x)$`
- Partial derivative: `$partial(f(x, y), x)$`
- Definite integral: `$integral(f(x), x, 0, 1)$`
- Limit: `$limit(sin(x) \\ x, x, 0)$`

## Aggregates

- Summation: `$sum(i^2, i, 1, n)$`
- Product: `$prod(i, i, 1, n)$`

## Display Math

$$
integral(exp(-x^2), x, -INFINITY, INFINITY)
$$
